In a statement, the President of the United States addresses the issue of the rise of anti-Semitism and the recent terrorist attack on a kosher supermarket in Paris. He affirms America's commitment to speaking out against anti-Semitism and announces that the United Nations General Assembly will gather to discuss this issue, at the request of the United States and 36 other nations. The President emphasizes that anti-Semitic attacks threaten not only the Jewish community but also the values of pluralism, diversity, and the freedoms of religion and expression. He believes that combating anti-Semitism is essential for the protection of human rights and fundamental freedoms for all individuals, and calls on every nation, region, and community to do their part. The President also urges the members of the UN General Assembly to support this fight against anti-Semitism.